        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 12 at 6:49PM EDT until August 12 at 7:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 649 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mayville,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
Lapeer County, including the following locations... Goodland
Township, Silverwood, Kings Mill, Burnside, and Attica.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
